# LPNW Plugin Development

## Plugin Architecture

Class-based modular architecture:

- `includes/` - Core classes (activator, deactivator, cron, models, matching engine, dispatcher)
- `feeds/` - Data feed classes, one per source. All extend LPNW_Feed_Base.
- `admin/` - WordPress admin panel pages and settings
- `public/` - Frontend shortcodes, dashboard, map integration
- `templates/` - Email HTML templates for Mautic

## Database Tables

Custom tables use $wpdb->prefix . 'lpnw_' prefix:
- lpnw_properties - Normalised property data from all sources
- lpnw_subscriber_preferences - User alert preferences (areas, price, types)
- lpnw_alert_queue - Queued and sent alerts
- lpnw_saved_properties - User bookmarks
- lpnw_feed_log - Feed run history and error tracking

## Feed Classes

Every data feed extends LPNW_Feed_Base and implements:
- fetch() - Pull raw data from API/source
- parse($raw_data) - Normalise into property schema
- get_source_name() - Return source identifier string

## Key Patterns

```php
// Always use prepare for queries
$wpdb->get_results($wpdb->prepare(
    "SELECT * FROM {$wpdb->prefix}lpnw_properties WHERE postcode LIKE %s",
    $postcode_prefix . '%'
));

// Always use WordPress HTTP API
$response = wp_remote_get($url, ['timeout' => 30]);
if (is_wp_error($response)) { /* handle */ }
$body = wp_remote_retrieve_body($response);
```

## NW Postcode Prefixes

For filtering data to Northwest England: M, L, PR, BB, LA, BL, OL, SK, WA, WN, CW, CH, CA, FY
